-- Itochu Agrees With Echelon to Develop, Sell Smart Grid Equipment in Japan
-- B y   S t u a r t   B i g g s
-- 2011-02-10T01:53:22Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-10/itochu-agrees-with-echelon-to-develop-sell-smart-grid-equipment-in-japan.html
  Itochu Corp ., Japan’s fourth-biggest
trading company, agreed with  San Jose , California-based  Echelon
Corp . to develop and sell the U.S. company’s smart grid
equipment and software.  Itochu will focus initially on selling Echelon’s products
in Japan before developing new applications for the firm’s smart
grid servers and software, Echelon said yesterday in a
 statement . Financial details weren’t disclosed.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Stuart Biggs in Tokyo at 
 sbiggs3@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Reed Landberg at 
 landberg@bloomberg.net . 